259
00:26:57,220 --> 00:26:58,764
-Hello.
-Dr. Glaser.

260
00:26:58,847 --> 00:27:02,059
You have reached
the office of Dr. Dorothy Glaser.

261
00:27:02,142 --> 00:27:04,144
Please leave your name...

262
00:27:22,245 --> 00:27:23,246
Hello?

263
00:27:23,288 --> 00:27:24,456
Jackie?

264
00:27:26,833 --> 00:27:28,293
Yeah?

265
00:27:28,377 --> 00:27:31,922
Jackie, don't hang up, please. This is Peter.

266
00:27:32,005 --> 00:27:35,884
I want to explain about the other day.
There was a reason...

267
00:27:37,386 --> 00:27:40,555
I had a very good reason
for doing what I did.

268
00:27:41,181 --> 00:27:42,766
I...

269
00:27:42,849 --> 00:27:48,021
Look, you know I'm very fond of you.
I didn't mean to hurt you. It was...

270
00:27:49,314 --> 00:27:50,816
It was some illness.

271
00:27:50,899 --> 00:27:52,943
Listen, I feel funny
talking on the phone about this.

272
00:27:53,026 --> 00:27:54,903
Better be a hell of a good reason.

273
00:27:54,945 --> 00:27:57,823
Let's meet. Can you? Tonight?

274
00:27:57,906 --> 00:28:01,618
You wanna get together tonight?
Meet somewhere?

275
00:28:01,701 --> 00:28:03,954
Well, I can't for a couple of hours.

276
00:28:04,246 --> 00:28:05,247
Fine. Fine.

277
00:28:05,789 --> 00:28:07,999
Let's just say 9:00. Mondo Cane.

278
00:28:09,209 --> 00:28:10,961
All right.

279
00:28:11,002 --> 00:28:12,379
9:00.

280
00:28:12,462 --> 00:28:15,298
Great. Great. Okay. I'll see you then.

281
00:28:15,382 --> 00:28:16,633
Bye bye.

282
00:29:36,379 --> 00:29:38,006
Who's there?

283
00:29:43,053 --> 00:29:44,554
Who is it?

284
00:31:21,026 --> 00:31:23,278
He is wondering,

285
00:31:23,320 --> 00:31:25,864
"How did she get in here?"

286
00:31:26,323 --> 00:31:28,700
And he is realizing

287
00:31:28,783 --> 00:31:32,662
that he let her in, as she is his lover.

288
00:31:32,746 --> 00:31:36,583
His most passionate mistress.

289
00:31:36,666 --> 00:31:38,918
And he is realizing

290
00:31:39,002 --> 00:31:42,464
that she is a jealous mistress.

291
00:32:14,871 --> 00:32:15,997
Yes.

292
00:32:41,773 --> 00:32:43,066
Alva.

293
00:32:46,611 --> 00:32:48,071
Alva.

294
00:32:50,990 --> 00:32:52,617
Alva!

295
00:32:54,536 --> 00:32:56,996
Alva!

296
00:32:58,915 --> 00:33:00,875
Alva!

297
00:33:01,918 --> 00:33:03,378
Alva!

298
00:33:04,003 --> 00:33:05,130
Alva!

299
00:33:14,931 --> 00:33:16,474
There you are!

300
00:33:30,947 --> 00:33:33,825
I'm looking for it, Mr. Loew. I'm looking!

301
00:33:35,535 --> 00:33:38,079
What the hell is he doing in here?

302
00:33:38,121 --> 00:33:40,081
I have a gun.

303
00:33:40,123 --> 00:33:42,959
If you hurt me, I'm gonna use it.

304
00:33:43,001 --> 00:33:46,171
What the fuck is going on?

305
00:33:46,254 --> 00:33:48,214
I don't know, I mean...

306
00:33:48,298 --> 00:33:52,677
I'm doing all I can.
Maybe the contract was lost.

307
00:33:52,761 --> 00:33:54,637
Don't come near me!

308
00:33:55,430 --> 00:33:57,974
I'm telling Mr. Langdon about this.

309
00:33:58,016 --> 00:34:01,478
And I swear I'm gonna use my gun
if you ever touch me.

310
00:34:02,771 --> 00:34:04,230
Just once.

311
00:34:04,314 --> 00:34:06,274
No. No, Alva, I'm sorry.

312
00:34:07,817 --> 00:34:09,486
I didn't mean...

313
00:34:09,569 --> 00:34:10,653
I'm sorry.

314
00:34:19,537 --> 00:34:21,372
You all right, honey?

315
00:34:22,665 --> 00:34:23,833
Yeah.

316
00:34:38,640 --> 00:34:42,685
Nothing like a little office trauma
to keep things interesting.

317
00:34:43,937 --> 00:34:46,147
The chase was my favorite part.

318
00:34:46,189 --> 00:34:48,566
Pete hurdling over those desks.

319
00:34:50,568 --> 00:34:52,654
Well, you weren't there for the grand finale.

320
00:34:52,695 --> 00:34:55,365
She asked me for a raise.
Can you believe it?

321
00:34:55,448 --> 00:34:57,784
She actually does keep a gun
in that little bag of hers.

322
00:34:57,867 --> 00:34:58,868
-Get out of here.
-No, really!

323
00:34:58,952 --> 00:35:02,497
Well, she takes the subway into Pelham
every night, I don't blame the kid.

324
00:35:02,539 --> 00:35:06,084
She asked me for a raise
for getting chased into the ladies' room.

325
00:35:06,167 --> 00:35:07,752
Well, I think she deserves it, Sidney.

326
00:35:08,086 --> 00:35:10,296
You can take it out of Attila's paycheck.

327
00:35:10,380 --> 00:35:12,090
Fuck you!

328
00:35:12,173 --> 00:35:13,758
One question, Peter.

329
00:35:13,842 --> 00:35:18,555
Is my name written anywhere
on the bathroom wall, and what did it say?

330
00:36:57,195 --> 00:36:59,906
What is happening to me?

331
00:37:45,368 --> 00:37:50,707
I had a difficult day yesterday.

332
00:37:52,917 --> 00:37:54,752
Got a little upset

333
00:37:56,504 --> 00:37:58,047
at the office.

334
00:37:58,798 --> 00:38:01,009
Do you want to talk about it?

335
00:38:02,885 --> 00:38:07,682
Well, it's just,
there's this contract we're trying to locate.

336
00:38:16,816 --> 00:38:18,317
Shouldn't...

337
00:38:19,068 --> 00:38:20,778
If a company...

338
00:38:21,529 --> 00:38:23,573
If a literary agency

339
00:38:24,615 --> 00:38:27,243
makes a copy of every contract,

340
00:38:28,661 --> 00:38:32,582
of every single contract
it makes with a client,

341
00:38:34,167 --> 00:38:36,335
and then puts it in a file,

342
00:38:37,253 --> 00:38:39,422
in the appropriate file,

343
00:38:43,426 --> 00:38:45,511
shouldn't the copy

344
00:38:46,929 --> 00:38:49,015
be in that file?

345
00:38:50,391 --> 00:38:51,476
Yes, I suppose it should.

346
00:38:51,559 --> 00:38:53,144
It should, right?

347
00:38:53,227 --> 00:38:54,437
-Yes.
-Right?

348
00:38:59,400 --> 00:39:02,278
Yep, yep, yep, yep.

349
00:39:04,322 --> 00:39:06,991
Unless, of course,
it's somehow been misfiled.

350
00:39:07,408 --> 00:39:08,618
Misfiled?

351
00:39:08,659 --> 00:39:10,161
Yes, misfiled.

352
00:39:11,496 --> 00:39:14,999
Sometimes, somebody puts a document
in the wrong file,

353
00:39:15,083 --> 00:39:16,459
and then it's misfiled.

354
00:39:16,501 --> 00:39:18,544
It makes it much harder to find.

355
00:39:18,628 --> 00:39:21,255
Who? Who? What do you mean? Who?

356
00:39:21,464 --> 00:39:23,841
I don't know who exactly.

357
00:39:24,050 --> 00:39:25,093
You don't?

358
00:39:25,134 --> 00:39:26,552
No, I don't.

359
00:39:27,720 --> 00:39:30,515
Whoever filed it in the first place, but...

360
00:39:30,598 --> 00:39:34,644
For God's sakes, Peter, I am not telling you
one single thing you don't already know.

361
00:39:34,727 --> 00:39:37,855
How could somebody misfile something?

362
00:39:39,065 --> 00:39:42,276
What could be easier? It's all alphabetical.

363
00:39:42,318 --> 00:39:45,738
You just put it in the right file,

364
00:39:45,822 --> 00:39:48,449
according to alphabetical order.

365
00:39:48,491 --> 00:39:51,828
You know,
"A," "B," "C," "D," "E," "F," "G..."

366
00:39:51,911 --> 00:39:55,414
-Peter.
-"H," "I," "J," "K," "L," "M," "N," "0," "P..."

367
00:39:55,498 --> 00:39:57,625
-Peter!
-"Q," "R," "S," "T,"

368
00:39:57,667 --> 00:40:00,128
-"U," "V," "W," "X," "Y," "Z."
-Oh, Jesus!

369
00:40:01,671 --> 00:40:03,673
That's all you have to do!

370
00:40:05,174 --> 00:40:07,593
Very good. You know your alphabet.

371
00:40:07,718 --> 00:40:10,179
I've never misfiled anything!

372
00:40:10,221 --> 00:40:12,014
Not once! Not one time!

373
00:40:12,849 --> 00:40:14,851
I'm sure that you didn't.

374
00:40:18,646 --> 00:40:20,356
I want to know, really. Who did?

375
00:40:20,439 --> 00:40:23,192
I cannot possibly tell you that.

376
00:40:24,277 --> 00:40:25,361
You can't?

377
00:40:25,403 --> 00:40:26,863
No, I can't.

378
00:40:29,657 --> 00:40:32,243
And you call yourself a psychiatrist.

379
00:40:45,256 --> 00:40:47,800
It's kind of bright in here, isn't it?

380
00:41:15,453 --> 00:41:17,246
He is so eccentric.

381
00:41:23,586 --> 00:41:25,129
Yes, Mr. Loew?

382
00:41:26,422 --> 00:41:29,508
Actually, she's just leaving, Mr. Loew.

383
00:41:29,592 --> 00:41:32,637
Sure. Alva, Mr. Loew would like to see you.

384
00:41:39,101 --> 00:41:40,645
Come in, Alva.

385
00:41:42,438 --> 00:41:45,691
I hope you're not still angry at me
about the other day, Alva.

386
00:41:45,775 --> 00:41:48,653
I apologized and I honestly meant it.

387
00:41:49,987 --> 00:41:51,364
Pistachio?

388
00:41:53,199 --> 00:41:56,327
Yeah, that mescaline. Wow.

389
00:41:56,410 --> 00:41:58,454
Does strange stuff.

390
00:42:00,206 --> 00:42:02,667
I'll never do that again. Jeez.

391
00:42:03,834 --> 00:42:06,087
Yeah, I know. I did it once.

392
00:42:06,128 --> 00:42:07,672
Did you? Did you?

393
00:42:07,755 --> 00:42:09,590
Yeah, just once, in high school.

394
00:42:12,843 --> 00:42:14,303
High school.

395
00:42:15,054 --> 00:42:16,597
Yes. Yes.

396
00:42:17,890 --> 00:42:19,892
Those were the days, eh, Alva?

397
00:42:20,142 --> 00:42:21,269
Yeah.

398
00:42:25,815 --> 00:42:27,942
So. Why...

399
00:42:28,651 --> 00:42:29,819
Why do you have your coat on?

400
00:42:31,112 --> 00:42:33,322
Well, I'm leaving. It's 5:00.

401
00:42:35,283 --> 00:42:39,912
But you know, Alva, you still haven't found
that contract yet, have you?

402
00:42:39,996 --> 00:42:42,832
Mr. Loew, there are 15 Der Spiegel files.

403
00:42:42,873 --> 00:42:44,625
It's all I do all day. I mean, I...

404
00:42:44,667 --> 00:42:47,211
But you haven't found it yet, Alva.

405
00:42:49,547 --> 00:42:51,841
Now, don't you think
it would be a good idea to stay late?

406
00:42:53,009 --> 00:42:55,094
Maybe work a little overtime?

407
00:42:55,177 --> 00:42:56,512
My eyes are killing me.

408
00:42:59,140 --> 00:43:01,350
Well, I was also thinking today

409
00:43:01,434 --> 00:43:04,854
that maybe you could
put somebody else on the job for a while.

410
00:43:05,938 --> 00:43:08,816
Or another secretary to help me out.

411
00:43:08,858 --> 00:43:10,359
I mean, you know, to make the job easier.

412
00:43:14,238 --> 00:43:15,531
Alva,

413
00:43:17,616 --> 00:43:21,037
there is no one else in this entire office

414
00:43:21,078 --> 00:43:25,374
that I could possibly ask
to share such a horrible job.

415
00:43:25,416 --> 00:43:28,377
You're the lowest
on the totem pole here, Alva.

416
00:43:28,461 --> 00:43:29,879
The lowest.

417
00:43:29,920 --> 00:43:32,048
Do you realize that?

418
00:43:32,089 --> 00:43:36,135
Every other secretary who's been here
has been here longer than you, Alva.

419
00:43:36,218 --> 00:43:37,803
Every one.

420
00:43:37,887 --> 00:43:39,430
And even if there was someone here

421
00:43:39,513 --> 00:43:42,308
who was here just one day longer than you,

422
00:43:42,391 --> 00:43:44,018
I still wouldn't ask that person

423
00:43:44,060 --> 00:43:45,811
to partake in such a miserable job

424
00:43:45,895 --> 00:43:48,564
as long as you are around.

425
00:43:48,647 --> 00:43:49,690
That's right, Alva.

426
00:43:50,649 --> 00:43:53,611
It's a horrible, horrible job.

427
00:43:53,694 --> 00:43:56,447
Sifting through old contract
after old contract.

428
00:43:57,782 --> 00:44:01,118
I couldn't think of a more horrible job
if I wanted to.

429
00:44:01,202 --> 00:44:04,163
And you have to do it. You have to.

430
00:44:04,246 --> 00:44:05,915
Or I'll fire you. Do you understand?

431
00:44:07,958 --> 00:44:09,210
Do you?

432
00:44:10,419 --> 00:44:11,545
Yes.

433
00:44:16,717 --> 00:44:17,843
Good.

434
00:44:22,223 --> 00:44:25,309
Then there's no problem then. Is there?

435
00:44:35,820 --> 00:44:38,447
Don't you want to use your gun, Alva?

436
00:45:03,139 --> 00:45:04,265
Hey.

437
00:45:05,141 --> 00:45:06,600
Here you go.

438
00:45:13,190 --> 00:45:15,526
Hey, man. You forgot your food.

439
00:45:27,329 --> 00:45:29,498
I hate interrupted love affairs, don't you?

440
00:45:29,540 --> 00:45:33,752
How much nicer when the outside world
doesn't interfere with the pleasure.

441
00:45:37,173 --> 00:45:40,801
You were so right
to put yourself into my hands, Peter.

442
00:45:41,385 --> 00:45:44,680
I'm the only one
who can put you out of your misery.

443
00:45:45,556 --> 00:45:48,893
Tell me how much you love me, my angel.

444
00:45:49,852 --> 00:45:52,521
Whisper it to me. Just once.

445
00:45:53,814 --> 00:45:55,483
Please.

446
00:45:55,524 --> 00:45:57,067
Just once.

447
00:45:57,151 --> 00:45:58,694
Oh, just once.

448
00:46:01,113 --> 00:46:04,867
I know you do.
I can read your mind, my love.

449
00:46:04,909 --> 00:46:07,786
I can see it in your actions.

450
00:46:07,870 --> 00:46:11,999
You can't get through the day
without thinking about me, can you?

451
00:46:16,212 --> 00:46:18,881
Tell me you love me.

452
00:46:21,967 --> 00:46:23,177
Tell me.

453
00:46:23,219 --> 00:46:24,553
Yes.

454
00:46:25,763 --> 00:46:26,889
Yes.

455
00:46:30,893 --> 00:46:32,770
Tell me how much you love me.

456
00:46:32,853 --> 00:46:33,938
Yes.

457
00:46:35,731 --> 00:46:37,399
Tell me.

458
00:46:37,483 --> 00:46:38,901
I love you.

459
00:46:40,569 --> 00:46:42,238
I love you.

460
00:46:56,001 --> 00:46:57,419
I love you.

461
00:47:22,611 --> 00:47:26,282
That was so clever of you. "Mescaline."

462
00:47:30,619 --> 00:47:32,955
How did you ever think of that?

463
00:47:34,123 --> 00:47:35,624
I don't know.

464
00:47:37,626 --> 00:47:40,504
Oh, but why should I be so surprised.

465
00:47:41,589 --> 00:47:44,091
My little literary genius.

466
00:47:50,639 --> 00:47:53,851
I knew you could keep our passion a secret.

467
00:48:04,737 --> 00:48:06,947
Sweet dreams, my angel.

468
00:48:38,312 --> 00:48:39,730
What's that?

469
00:48:41,148 --> 00:48:42,900
Wanna join me?

470
00:48:43,025 --> 00:48:44,985
Well, absolutely, love.

471
00:48:46,695 --> 00:48:48,489
Watch your step.

472
00:48:49,782 --> 00:48:53,160
Come on, now. Don't do that.
I have to go to work.

473
00:48:53,202 --> 00:48:55,162
Stop it, now! Come on!

474
00:49:35,077 --> 00:49:37,830
Thank God it's Friday.
That's all I've got to say.

475
00:49:37,955 --> 00:49:41,667
All I'm gonna do this weekend
is stay home and sleep.

476
00:49:42,626 --> 00:49:44,378
This place is driving me crazy.

477
00:49:44,420 --> 00:49:45,754
Morning everyone.

478
00:49:45,838 --> 00:49:47,297
Good morning.

479
00:49:51,927 --> 00:49:54,346
I wonder what Alva's doing today.

480
00:49:59,852 --> 00:50:02,563
-Yes, Mr. Loew?
-Judy, would you send Alva in here, please?

481
00:50:02,604 --> 00:50:04,606
She called in sick today, Mr. Loew.

482
00:50:04,648 --> 00:50:08,068
-Did she?
-Yes, she said she had a very bad cold.

483
00:50:08,110 --> 00:50:10,362
A bad cold.

484
00:50:10,446 --> 00:50:11,947
Thanks, Judy.

485
00:50:15,075 --> 00:50:17,286
A bad cold.

486
00:50:18,328 --> 00:50:20,581
My, my, my.

487
00:50:27,671 --> 00:50:30,382
I am not going to work today, Mommy.

488
00:50:31,550 --> 00:50:32,718
My boss is a bastard.

489
00:50:33,302 --> 00:50:36,138
Don't you use
that kind of language in front of me.

490
00:50:36,180 --> 00:50:37,806
Well, it's true.

491
00:50:38,807 --> 00:50:42,478
-I hate him.
-Yes, "I hate him, I hate him."

492
00:50:42,561 --> 00:50:44,146
What do you think?

493
00:50:44,229 --> 00:50:46,732
That's an excuse not to go to work?

494
00:50:47,900 --> 00:50:50,778
You know how many people
hate their boss?

495
00:50:50,819 --> 00:50:55,115
I hate my boss,
but do I stay home and cry about it?

496
00:50:56,325 --> 00:50:58,202
I know. Mommy, but you...

497
00:50:58,285 --> 00:51:01,663
Listen, young lady.
You can't afford to lose that job.

498
00:51:01,705 --> 00:51:04,041
You'll get no more money
from your father and me.

499
00:51:04,124 --> 00:51:05,709
I'll just get another job.

500
00:51:05,793 --> 00:51:11,089
I'm late. Now, get dressed
and get your little ass into the city.

501
00:51:11,173 --> 00:51:12,633
-No.
-Now!

502
00:52:13,819 --> 00:52:15,487
What are you doing here?

503
00:52:16,071 --> 00:52:19,283
What, Alva?
I can hardly hear you through this window.

504
00:52:19,575 --> 00:52:21,702
What are you doing here?

505
00:52:21,743 --> 00:52:22,911
I heard you were sick.

506
00:52:23,370 --> 00:52:25,163
A terrible cold.

507
00:52:25,247 --> 00:52:26,331
I'm calling the police.

508
00:52:26,540 --> 00:52:27,666
The police?

509
00:52:27,749 --> 00:52:30,711
Alva! I'm here to call a truce, man. Look.

510
00:52:31,795 --> 00:52:34,715
I just took a $20 taxi ride
all the way up here

511
00:52:34,756 --> 00:52:38,594
so I could tell you I think it was wrong
the way I treated you yesterday.

512
00:52:39,011 --> 00:52:41,680
Now, is that an elaborate gesture or what?

513
00:52:41,763 --> 00:52:43,765
Plus, look. Soup!

514
00:52:59,907 --> 00:53:01,116
Hi.

515
00:53:02,034 --> 00:53:04,119
Mr. Loew, I stayed till one in the morning

516
00:53:04,202 --> 00:53:06,413
and I still couldn't find the contract.

517
00:53:06,455 --> 00:53:09,374
Oh, Alva, don't worry about it.
It's understandable. Really.

518
00:53:09,458 --> 00:53:13,420
Yeah, but I know how worried you were
about losing Mr. Heatherton as a client.

519
00:53:13,462 --> 00:53:16,256
Alva, right now,
what's most important is your health.

520
00:53:18,133 --> 00:53:19,968
